article.description: BOSTON (AP) -Bennet Davis led a balanced attack with 20 points and 10 rebounds as host Northeastern never trailed in defeating Boston University, 73-54.
article.headline: BOSTON (AP) -Bennet Davis led a balanced attack with 20 points and 10 rebounds as host Northeastern never trailed in defeating Boston University, 73-54.
article.linkText: BOSTON (AP) -Bennet Davis led a balanced attack with 20 points and 10 rebounds as host Northeastern never trailed in defeating Boston University, 73-54.
article.story: The Huskies (1-4) jumped out to a 12-0 lead as the Terriers (1-3) went scoreless for the first 3:36 until Ibrahim Konate broke BU's drought with a basket. Northeastern led by as many as 14 points throughout the opening half and led at the break, 46-32. Freshman Matt Janning scored eight of the team's first 15 points on 3-of-3 shooting, including two 3-pointers. He finished with 16 points. The Terriers, meanwhile, missed seven of their first eight shots and never recovered. BU made just 18 of 50 shots in the game, while Northeastern hit 26 of 51. The Terriers came back in the second half, going on a 8-0 run at one point to close the gap to 49-44, but Adrian Martinez and Bobby Kelly hit back-to-back 3-pointers to put the Huskies back up by double digits. Martinez hit his first five 3-pointers of the game and finished with 21 points. For the Terriers, senior Omari Peterkin led the way with 15 points and 14 rebounds for his first double-double of the season. Tyler Morris, one of the team's four freshman starters, had 14 points while fellow freshman starter Corey Lowe added 10. The victory was the first of Northeastern coach Bill Coen's career.
